    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Your Application for the Senior Dev Role\n\nDear [Candidate's Name],\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I wanted to take a moment to thank you for your interest in the Senior Dev role at our Austin office and for the effort you put into your application. We were truly impressed by your skills and passion for development, and we appreciate the time you invested in the interview process.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with a candidate whose experience aligns more closely with our current needs, particularly in AWS architectures. While this decision was difficult, we believe it is in the best interest of our team and the project at hand.\n\nI want to personally thank you for the engaging and insightful conversation we had during your technical interview. It was a pleasure to discuss your experiences and ideas with you, and I know you left with a sense of accomplishment. We enjoyed learning about your approach to problem-solving and your enthusiasm for technology.\n\nPlease know that your talent and dedication are highly regarded, and we encourage you to apply for future opportunities that match your expertise. We have no doubt that you will find success in your next endeavor.\n\nThank you once again for your interest in our company. We wish you all the best in your future career pursuits.",
